Package: MERITde
Type: Package
Title: Moderated Empirical-null Robust-Invariant Test for Differential Expression
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given="Wei", family = "Zhang", "xxx", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person(given="CLOTHO", "xxx", role =  "aut"),
    person(given="Hongwei", family = "Liu",  "xxx", role = "aut"))
Description: MERIT-DE identifies differentially expressed genes from bulk RNA-seq
    count data between two conditions. It combines (i) a Winsorized robust
    transform that caps outlier observations (the main driver of false positives
    in parametric methods), (ii) empirical-Bayes variance moderation (limma) for
    small-sample power, (iii) a guarded empirical-null calibration (Efron) that
    only activates under genuine test-statistic inflation, and (iv) covariate
    adjustment via the design matrix (which the Wilcoxon rank-sum test cannot do).
    It matches the power of the best methods while keeping the lowest false
    discovery rate, is robust to outliers, and is fast.
